com.example.moodmobile

Class Mood

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.moodmobile.Mood
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Moodable

    public class Mood
extends java.lang.Object
implements Moodable
    This is the main class used to implement the moods in the application. The main parameters used for this class are as follows:
    • message: Optional reason
    • date: Date when the mood was posted
    • feeling: Mandatory emotion
    • socialSituation: Optional situation
    • moodImage: Optional image to be attached
    • username: Name of the user that posted the mood
    • location: Location stored as string
    • latitude: Latitude of the mood
    • longitude: Longitude of the mood
    • id: ID of the mood returned by ElasticSearch
    The location is stored as a string so that it can be stored as a geo_point type object in ElasticSearch to use when searching for nearby moods.
